          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,RCA,33,177,1983",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,RCA,33,177,1983",
                    "doi": "10.1524/ract.1983.33.4.177",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "RCA",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "33",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "177"
                      },
                      "date": 1983
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  NSR Index=1983Kl10"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ISOCY"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERKFK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "INTB",
                "BCINT",
                "MOMIX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". For each irradiation the",
                "the individual mn-54 calibration was used. Furthermore,",
                "for all alpha-irradiated sources the efficiencies",
                "were determined. Leaving off all values which were",
                "obviously too small due to bad positioning we",
                "calculated on average value of X-ray energy (5.41 keV)",
                "which was used to calculate the cross sections for",
                "protons, deuterons, He-3-induced reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " gamma-ray spectra aiming at the 835 keV gamma-",
                "ray of 54Mn were measured by means of two different",
                "Ge(Li) -detectors (11.2% efficiency, 1.9 keV resolution",
                "and 15% efficiency, 1.78 keV resolution, respectively,",
                "for the 1332 keV gamma-ray of 60Co)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The sources were measured directly in front of",
                "a liquid nitrogen cooled Si(LI) -detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Foils of natural vanadium(purity > 99.8%)with",
                "thicknesses of 8.1 and 9.9mg/cm**2, respectively, have",
                "been irradiated at various energies with protons,",
                "deuterons,He-3 and alpha-particles in the internal",
                "beam of the Karlsruhe Isochronous Cyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/by Authors/ In case of production of V-49 by alpha-",
                "irradiation of natural vanadium foils such a",
                "calibration activity is produced in the same targets by",
                "means of an (alpha,n)-reaction leading to Mn-54. This",
                "nucleus  decays by electron capture mainly to the",
                "834.8 keV level of Cr-54 which de-excites by the",
                "respective ground state transition. The ratio of",
                "emitted k-X-rays to gamma-rays has been determined",
                "experimentally.",
                "Consequently, the absolute X-ray intensities for Mn-54",
                "and from this also for V-49 can be determined from the",
                "same target foil ruling out uncertainties from the",
                "geometrical setup of source and detector and from the",
                "absorption."
              ]
            }
          ],
